  "2026-07-13T22:03:50.226Z",codex-root,"Scope note 2026-07-13: when pm-ju83 lands, extend this task's SDK reference and migration work with relationship-kind registration, immutable relationship events, bounded adjacency/path/closure/impact queries, cursor and streaming contracts, compact CLI and MCP projections, explain/cost envelopes, legacy-kind migration, and shell pipeline examples. Link implementation docs to pm-96h7 and validate with the existing docs gates."
  "2026-07-17T13:10:37.141Z",codex-root,"Documentation progress: SDK and relationship-graph references now cover public actionability, workspace assembly, semantic traversal, governance findings, layering boundaries, and a non-PM domain reuse pattern. Docs gate passes."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:20.846Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: linked docs-skills gate passed; SDK and relationship graph docs explain public actionability, assembly, semantic traversal, governance findings, layering, VCS/company reuse, bounds, and migration semantics. Strict 100% docstring coverage, docs links, package tarball, and runnable installed SDK examples pass. This documentation tranche is complete; the task remains open because its acceptance follows every future promoted primitive in pm-usfg/pm-ju83."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T10:06:40.159Z",maintainer-agent,"Documentation-target expansion 2026-07-18 (PR#587): the promoted-primitive set this reference must cover grew by the SDK relationship event platform — registerRelationshipKinds/RelationshipKindRegistry (extension-contributed kinds with direction/inverse/ordering/cardinality/lifecycle/aliases/version), RelationshipEventLog/RelationshipEventStore bounded immutable streams + reducer projections (in-memory and durable, checkpoint boundary semantics), workspace graph assembly merging active package ontologies, and host-bound SDK injection into extension command handlers (context.sdk with caller authorship). PR#587 seeded docs/SDK.md + docs/EXTENSIONS.md deltas and packages/pm-vcs/README.md is the runnable exemplar to cite; this item still owns the consolidated reference + migration notes. Prior-tranche targets unchanged (graph/analytics + governance subpath modules from PR#579/#580/#581)."
